swap(uint256,uint256,address[],address,u.details: : This function supports both ETH and ERC20 tokens as input and output. The address 0xEeeeeEeeeEeEeeEeEeEeeEEEeeeeEeeeeeeeEEeE is used as a placeholder for ETH. If the input token is ETH, it is replaced with the actual WETH address and `swapExactETHForTokensSupportingFeeOnTransferTokens` is called. If the output token is ETH, it is replaced with the actual WETH address and `swapExactTokensForETHSupportingFeeOnTransferTokens` is called. Otherwise, `swapExactTokensForTokensSupportingFeeOnTransferTokens` is called. If there is any ETH balance left in the contract, it is sent back to the caller. Requirements: - The `path` must have at least two addresses. - The sender must have approved this contract to spend the input tokens.

params.amountIn: The amount of input tokens to be sent.
params.amountOutMin: The minimum amount of output tokens that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.deadline: The time after which the swap is invalid.
params.path: An array of token addresses. The path[0] address is the input token and the last address is the output token.
params.to: The address to send the output tokens to.

updateSupplyAndAddLiquidity(uint256,uint.details: amountWETHDesired = 0 when adding liquidity with ETH

params.amountETHMin: The minimum amount of ETH/WETH the user wants to add as liquidity.
params.amountPonzioDesired: The amount of Ponzio token the user wants to add as liquidity.
params.amountPonzioMin: The minimum amount of Ponzio token the user wants to add as liquidity.
params.amountWETHDesired: The amount of WETH the user wants to add as liquidity.
params.to: The address to which the liquidity tokens will be minted.

returns.amountETH_: The actual amount of ETH (or equivalent) added as liquidity.
returns.amountPonzio_: The actual amount of Ponzio token added as liquidity.
returns.liquidity_: The amount of liquidity tokens minted.

LP_TOKEN().notice: Returns the address of the staking token.

PONZIO().notice: Returns the address of the Ponzio.

swap(uint256,uint256,address[],address,u.notice: Swaps a certain `amountIn` of a token for another token, ensuring a minimum output `amountOutMin`.

updateSupplyAndAddLiquidity(uint256,uint.notice: Update the supply of Ponzio and add liquidity to the pair.
